HEADWORD: dominicide
<hw>do*min"i*cide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>dominus</ets> master + <ets>caedere</ets> to cut down, kill.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of killing a master.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who kills his master.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dominick</ent>⟦br⟧
